Body:
Description: Can you provide more info on how Service Accounts are identified in the AD_ServiceAccounts Job. What the criteria that need to be satisfied to be able be captured in that report?
Thanks!

• The ADI1-Scan collects the servicePrincipalName & msDS-SupportedEncryptionTypes attributes (viewable in the ADI Query Settings > Custom Attributes)
    • servicePrincipalName (SPN) is what determines if an account is a "service account"

Looking at the where statements in the Analysis for that job 3 things point out. Underlined important parts.

FROM   [SA_ADInventory_ExtendedAttributes] ea

LEFT JOIN [SA_ADInventory_EffectiveGroupMembersView] egmv

ON    egmv.[MemberPrincipalId] = ea.[PrincipalId]

WHERE   egmv.[GroupObjectSid] IN (SELECT [ObjectSid] FROM #GroupSIDs) AND ea.[Name]='servicePrincipalName'

 

FROM  [SA_ADInventory_ExtendedAttributes] ea

WHERE [Name] = 'msds-supportedencryptiontypes'

AND  CAST([Value] AS int) > 7

 

 

FROM   [SA_ADInventory_UsersView] uv

JOIN   [SA_ADInventory_ExtendedAttributes] ea

ON    uv.[PrincipalId] = ea.[PrincipalId]

LEFT JOIN #admins a

ON    uv.[PrincipalId] = a.[PrincipalId]

LEFT JOIN #vuln v

ON    uv.[PrincipalId] = v.[PrincipalId]

WHERE   ea.[Name]='servicePrincipalName' AND uv.IsDeleted = 0

 

if it is not deleted and has a name attribute of msds-supportedencryptiontypes and another attribute of servicePrincipleName It makes the cut as a Service Account.
Next Steps Updated: Awaiting response from customer if they require any assistance.
What We've Learned Updated: The customer wants to identify the criteria used for checking if an account is service account in AD.
